abstract: The Toyota Prius, which dominates the U.S. hybrid car market, will face its most serious challenger this year as Honda introduces the Insight hybrid.
snippet: The Toyota Prius, which dominates the U.S. hybrid car market, will face its most serious challenger this year as Honda introduces the Insight hybrid.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT  The Toyota Prius, which currently dominates the American hybrid car market, will face its most serious challenger this year.

headline.main: Honda Unveils a Cheaper Hybrid Challenger to Toyota’s Top-Selling Prius
headline.print_headline: Honda Unveils a Cheaper Hybrid Challenger to Toyota’s Top-Selling Prius

abstract: Several start-up automakers are in hot pursuit of electric-powered vehicles, but they face an uphill road as they challenge major car companies like Toyota and General Motors in the race for the green car market, The Associated Press reported.
lead_paragraph: Several start-up automakers are in hot pursuit of electric-powered vehicles, but they face an uphill road as they challenge major car companies like Toyota and General Motors in the race for the green car market, The Associated Press reported.

headline.main: E-Car Start-Ups Try to Compete With Major Companies
